                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>A growing number of China\u2019s most prominent business leaders have disappeared from public view in recent years.  These events have created speculation about the forces reshaping the country\u2019s corporate elite. Famous technology pioneers and prominent real estate developers, have stepped down from executive roles, disappeared from social media, or been detained without immediate explanation.</p>\n           <p>Analysts suspect Beijing\u2019s anti-corruption campaigns and regulatory crackdowns as key factors. Authorities have tightened oversight of industries such as technology, finance, and property development citing concerns about systemic risk and national security. In several high-profile cases, executives later reemerged to acknowledge investigations into alleged financial crimes or regulatory violations. Others have faced formal charges, while a few have remained largely out of sight.</p>\n           <p>The uncertainty has disrupted investors and led to questions about transparency in the world\u2019s second-largest economy. International markets have reacted sharply to sudden leadership changes at major firms, demonstrating the importance of China policy around the globe.</p>\n           <p>Chinese officials maintain that the investigations are necessary to promote \u201ccommon prosperity\u201d and ensure long-term stability. But for many observers, the pattern of disappearing executives highlights the delicate balance between private enterprise and state authority in modern China.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Firefighting is widely regarded as one of the most physically demanding professions, and departments across the country require candidates to pass rigorous physical ability tests before joining the ranks. The exams are designed to simulate real-life emergency scenarios and ensure recruits can handle the demands of the job.</p>\n           <p>One of the most common assessments is the Candidate Physical Ability Test (CPAT), which includes eight timed events. Applicants must climb stairs while carrying weighted equipment, drag charged hoses across a set distance, and raise and extend ladders. It is also required to perform forcible entry simulations such as using weighted sleds, navigating dark, confined spaces, and rescuing a life-sized mannequin.</p>\n           <p>Strength, endurance, agility, and cardiovascular fitness are all measured during the process. Candidates often wear a weighted vest to replicate the protective gear firefighters typically carry. The test is completed in under 10 minutes in many departments, requiring both speed and stamina.</p>\n           <p>Fire officials say the standards are essential for public and firefighter safety. Proper preparation such as strength training and aerobic conditioning, is strongly recommended for anyone considering a career in this sector.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>From churchgoers in Venezuela who roller-skate to children in Germany who throw shoes, Europe is alive each December with traditions that are quirky and cherished. In Catalonia, Spain, families place a smiling log called Caga Ti\u00f3 in their homes and \u201cfeed\u201d it for weeks before Christmas. On Christmas Eve, children beat the log with sticks while singing, urging it to deliver sweets and small gifts.</p>\n           <p>In Austria and parts of southern Germany, the festive season has a darker side. Men dressed as horned Krampus creatures walk through town squares, rattling chains and playfully chasing spectators, reviving a centuries-old Alpine legend meant to frighten naughty children.</p>\n           <p>In Ukraine, Christmas trees shine with artificial spider webs, inspired by a legend in which spiders spun silver threads to help a poor family celebrate. Meanwhile in Norway, households hide their brooms on Christmas Eve to prevent mischievous spirits said to fly in the night sky.</p>\n           <p>These unusual customs showcase Europe\u2019s rich history of folklore, faith and fun\u2014reminding visitors that the magic of Christmas often lies in the delightfully unexpected. From Italy\u2019s gift-bearing witch La Befana to the Czech custom of tossing shoes to predict marriage, the continent embraces joyful eccentricity in this festive winter season.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
